# =============================================================================
# Instant Re-Play — environment
# =============================================================================
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (the default): leave DATABASE_URL UNSET.
# With no DATABASE_URL, the app uses PGlite — an embedded WASM Postgres that
# persists to ./.data/pglite on disk. No cloud, no services, no setup:
# `npm run dev` just works and your log survives restarts (FR-20).
#
# PRODUCTION (Neon): set DATABASE_URL to your Neon Postgres connection string.
# When DATABASE_URL is present the app talks to Neon instead of PGlite, using
# the exact same Drizzle schema and queries (PGlite *is* Postgres).
#
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST/DBNAME?sslmode=require"
#
# Deploy-time migration for Neon (run once against the Neon database):
#   DATABASE_URL="postgresql://..." npm run db:migrate
#
# Optional: override where the local PGlite store lives (default ./.data/pglite)
# PGLITE_DATA_DIR="./.data/pglite"
#
# =============================================================================
# SHARED LOGIN — Supabase magic-link auth + invite allowlist (feature: shared-login)
# =============================================================================
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (the default): leave all three UNSET. With no Supabase env,
# a dev-only bypass is active (NODE_ENV !== "production" AND no Supabase config)
# so `npm run dev` and the tests run as a synthetic invited "dev@localhost" user
# and the log/stats/export all work with no Supabase project. This bypass is
# DEAD in production: on Vercel NODE_ENV=production forces real auth always.
#
# PRODUCTION: set all three. If the Supabase vars or ALLOWED_EMAILS are missing
# in production, the app FAILS CLOSED (denies access) rather than exposing the
# archive.
#
# Supabase project URL and anon (public-safe) key. Both are NEXT_PUBLIC_ because
# Supabase designs the anon key to ship to the browser (the server-side allowlist
# is the real gate). NEVER add a service-role key — nothing here needs one.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL="https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co"
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="YOUR-ANON-KEY"
#
# The invite allowlist: comma-separated, case-insensitive, whitespace-trimmed.
# SERVER-ONLY — never prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_ (it must not reach the client).
# A valid Supabase session is necessary but NOT sufficient; the email must be
# on this list. A missing/blank value means nobody is invited (fail closed).
# ALLOWED_EMAILS="owner@example.com, dad@example.com"
